<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agricultural Bank of China Opens Office in Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2903172094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1526 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2903172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, March 29 (XINHUA) -- The Agricultural 
Bank of China, one of China's four principal state-owned 
specialized banks, opened a representative office here today. 
  This was the bank's first representative office in Hong Kong 
and the fourth one opened abroad after Tokyo, Singapore and 
London. It is preparing for the establishment of the fifth one 
in New York, according to the bank's President Ma Yongwei. 
  The opening of the office was in line with China's open 
policy and the bank's own strategic plans to internationalize 
its operations and increase its overseas presence, Ma said. 
  He expressed that his bank would further strengthen, through 
co- operation, its relations with the financial community of 
Hong Kong and contribute to Hong Kong's prosperity and stability. 
  As one of the top 50 banks in the world, the agricultural 
bank now has 54,000 branch offices with 540,000 staff. Its 
total assets has come to 1.05 trillion renminbi (184 billion 
U.S. dollars). It also has correspondent banking arrangements 
with 244 overseas banks in 71 countries and regions. 

</TEXT>

