<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Insurance Company Restructures International Business </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK3003040594 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1209 GMT 
29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK3003040594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 29 (CNS)--The People's Insurance 
Company of China signed a document with its 44 branches today 
for reform of management to bring their business into line with 
the international insurance market. 
  General manager of the company Mr. Li Yumin said that he 
hoped the restructuring of the company's international opeations 
would help China's insurance business move in step with its 
international counterparts as soon as possible. The move is 
considered as a preparation in the insurance sector for the 
restoration of China's signatory status to the General Agreement 
on Tariffs and Trade. 
  According to the document, the company will to some extent 
allow autonomy to its branches for various measures to be 
adopted in accordance with their own business situation. The 
branches are free to implement measures in terms of insurance 
charge rate, insurance provisions and insurance cost while at 
the same time being responsible to the parent company in terms 
of profit, insurance premiums and indemnity. If a branch 
fulfills a particular set target, then it will be given a reward 
or a penalty if the case is the oposite. Mr Li said that he 
hoped this practice would help increase the revenue from 
premiums by 15 percent this year compared with that in the year 
before. 
  The insurance company founded on October 20, 1949 has an 
employment of 110,000 and premium revenue was RMB 49.96 billion 
[renminbi] last year, 35.6 percent up over the previous year. 
The total amount in indemnities paid at home and broad was 
valued at RMB 27.85 billion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

