<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   ARATS Official Views Talks With Taiwan Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003005994 Beijing China Radio International in Mandarin 
to Asia 0900 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW3003005994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing China Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After one day's recess, the Association for 
Relations Across the Taiwan Strait (ARATS) and Taiwan's Straits 
Exchange Foundation (SEF) resumed in Beijing in the morning of 
29 March comprehensive discussion of three routine topics, 
including fishing disputes. 
  After the meeting, Sun Yafu, deputy secretary-general of 
ARATS, said: During the discussion, both parties expressed their 
opinions about the crucial points of the three topics which need 
to be resolved. Both sides further exchanged their opinions and 
deepened their understanding. But the two sides have not yet 
reached a consensus on some issues that need to be resolved. 
  According to a suggestion raised by Xu Huiyou [Hsu Hui-yu], 
deputy secretary-general of SEF, both sides have decided through 
consultation to hold another comprehensive discussion on the 
morning of 30 March to give it another try. 
  It was learned that discussion of the three topics -- 
including cracking down on criminal activities committed at sea, 
as well as other topics concerning economic, scientific, and 
technological matters which were scheduled to be discussed by 
ARATS and SEF on 28 March -- were not conducted due to the 
absence of Shi Qiping [Shih Chi-ping], another deputy 
secretary-general of SEF. 

</TEXT>

