<H3> <TI>   CNA System Goes On-Line in Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2503150094 Taipei CNA in English 1337 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2503150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Stanley Cheung &amp; Benjamin Yeh] </F>
  [Text] Hong Kong, March 25 (CNA) -- Central News Agency 
made its mass-media news system available in Hong Kong Friday 
[25 March]. 
  Users of the system will be provided with round-the-clock 
coverage of Chinese- and English-language news, business reports 
and futures updates from around the world, and color photos. 
The service will be transmitted by telephone to the customers' 
computers. 
  The semi-official news agency will formally introduce the 
system to potential Hong Kong customers at a display in 
mid-April. 
  CNA soon will introduce to Hong Kong an on-time news 
service, 
which is already available in Taiwan. 

</TEXT>

