<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Heilongjiang Secretary Discusses Anticorruption Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2603081494 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2200 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2603081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the third plenary session of the provincial 
discipline inspection commission held on 25 March, Sun Weiben, 
secretary of the provincial party committee, pointed out: Party 
committees, governments, and discipline inspection and 
supervision organs at all levels should conscientiously 
implement the plans of the central authorities and of the 
provincial party committee on anticorruption work, and on the 
basis of consolidating the achievements we have made, conducted 
this year's anticorruption struggle in a sustained, in-depth, 
and more effective manner. 
  The third plenary session of the provincial discipline 
inspection commission held second meeting on the afternoon of 25 
March. Sun Weiben, secretary of the provincial party committee, 
gave a speech, entitled: "Submit Ourselves to and Serve the 
Overall Situation of the Whole's Party's Work and Conduct 
Anticorruption Struggle in a Sustained, In-Depth, and More 
Effective Manner. 
  Provincial Leaders, including Shao Qihui, Zhou Wenhua, Ma 
Guoliang, Tian Fengshan, Shan Rongfan, Li Qinglin, and Yu 
Jingchang attended the meeting. 
  Sun Weiben pointed out: Constantly and deeply fighting 
corruption is a strategic policy decision made by the party 
Central Committee after correctly appraising the previous stage 
of work, the further demand of deepening reform and accelerating 
development, the important guarantee for political and social 
stability, and the current strong desire and demand of cadres 
inside and outside the party. To this end, our party and 
government leading comrades at all levels must be soberly minded 
in this aspect. 
  Sun Weiben pointed out: This year the general demand of our 
province's anticorruption work is to comprehensively fulfill the 
three central tasks, to consolidate the achievement, and to 
carry it out in an in-depth and more effective way. To 
consolidate achievements means that we must grasp the 
anticorruption work which we started last year until good 
results are achieved; places which have achieved good results in 
this aspect should continue to improve their work. To pay 
attention to in-depth work means that we must resolutely 
straighten out and handle the problems which have been 
discovered and step up efforts to formulate and improve the 
relevant management regulations and preventive measures. To pay 
attention to effective results means that we must sum up and 
popularize the experiences and lessons gained in the previous 
stage of work and improve and strengthen work measures in an 
effort to achieve greater achievements. 
  Sun Weiben said: The current anticorruption struggle must be 
carried out in the course of accelerating the establishment of 
the socialist market economic structure. The work of fighting 
corruption and promoting honesty must be combined with the 
implementation of the major reform measures. In addition to 
providing conditions and a guarantee for the implementation of 
the four reform tasks through anticorruption struggle, we should 
also fundamentally check the appearance of corrupt phenomena by 
deepening reform and building systems so as to achieve results 
in bringing about a temporary solution and in getting at the 
root of the problem. Sun Weiben stressed: Taking a two-handed 
approach and being tough with both is a strategic principle and 
leadership method which our party has persistently upheld. 
According to the past experiences and lessons, the phenomenon 
of being tough with one hand and soft with the other hand will 
easily occur when the reform and economic work tasks are 
arduous. This year more reform measures will be issued, the 
reform strength will be strong, and risks will appear. Under 
such circumstance, we should all the more persist in taking a 
two-handed approach and be tough with both, and should 
strengthen leadership over the anticorruption struggle. 
Therefore, we should continue to implement the responsibility 
system in anticorruption work, strengthen supervision, 
inspection, and work guidance, and earnestly support discipline 
inspection and procuratorial organs to exercise their duties. 
  Provincial leaders, including Li Genshen, Xie Yong, Sun 
Kuiwen, Zhou Tienong, Yang Zhihai, and Ma Shuji, comrades of the 
leading group for building party style and administrative 
honesty of the provincial party committee, and principal 
responsible comrades of various provincial-level departments 
also attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

