<H3> <TI>   Jilin Builds Railways, Expressways, Ports to Outside World </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1903161794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1246 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1903161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Changchun, March 19 (XINHUA) -- Northeast China's 
Jilin Province is speeding up the construction of railways, 
expressways and ports to promote its economic cooperation with 
foreign countries and regions. 
  The province, with easy access to the sea through its 
borders 
with Russia and the People's Democratic Republic of Korea, is 
now quickening its building of four routes leading to the 
outside world. 
  The four routes, mainly railways and expressways, will link 
up with China's two railways leading to Russia and Korea and 
extended to port cities of Russia and Korea. 
  The province is also renovating its two airports and 
increasing domestic and international flights and routes. So 
far four air routes have been opened with irregular flights from 
Changchun to Hong Kong and to cities of Russia, Japan, and the 
Republic of Korea. 

</TEXT>

