<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four Financial Laws, Regulations Promulgated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK3003024594 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1433 GMT 
29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK3003024594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 29 (CNS)--Four financial laws and 
regulations including a "Law for the People's Bank of China" 
will come into force, according to a meeting held by the 
People's Bank of China on work on national financial laws and 
regulations. 
  The Vice President of the central bank Mr. Yin Jieyan said 
that the draft laws and regulations namely the "Law for the 
People's Bank of China", a "Banking Law for the People's 
Republic of China", an "Insurance Law" and a "Law on Notes", all 
of which were drawn up by the central bank have been submitted 
to the State Council for appraisal and discussion before going 
for deliberation and approval by the Standing Committee of the 
National People's Congress. It is expected the laws and 
regulations will come into force in the second half of this year. 
  The "Law for People's Bank of China" is aimed at 
safeguarding 
the stability of the currency and ensuring smooth operation of 
the financial market in a bid to improve the financial system to 
serve economic development. The law states that the central 
bank will set up a committee for monetary policy in order to 
stabilize the value of the currency and prevent inflation. The 
"Banking Law for the People's Republic of China" is aimed at 
governing the commercial banks in a bid to make them operate 
smoothly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

