<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing Meets U.S. Chamber Visitors From Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003084894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0826 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
Li Lanqing met here this morning with a delegation from the 
American Chamber of Commerce in Hong Kong headed by its chairman 
Gerald Murdock. 
  The two sides exchanged views on issues of common interest 
such as Sino-U.S. economic and trade relations. 
  Li said that the United States is the largest developed 
country in the world while China is the largest developing one, 
adding that the development of Sino-U.S. economic and trade 
relations is not only beneficial to the two sides, but will also 
have an enormous influence on the world economy as a whole. 
  The nine-member U.S. delegation arrived here on March 29 at 
the invitation of the China Council for the Promotion of 
International Trade. 

</TEXT>

