<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Officials Agree on 3-Point Principle </H4>
<F P=102> SK3103122294 Seoul YONHAP in English 1151 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3103122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 31 (YONHAP) -- The South Korean and 
Chinese presidents agreed in their recent meeting in Beijing 
that they do not want any pressure put on North Korea over the 
nuclear question, Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Wu Jianmin 
said on Thursday. 
  In a routine press briefing for both Chinese and foreign 
press members, Wu said Presidents Kim Yong-sam and Jiang Zemin 
agreed on a three-point principle in connection with the Korean 
situation. 
  The principle was the maintenance of peace and stability on 
the Korean peninsula, resolution of the North Korean nuclear 
question through dialogue, and non-use of pressure against North 
Korea over the nuclear issue. 
  Reiterating China's opposition to any resolution by the U.N. 
Security Council, spokesman Wu said, "since dialogue alone will 
be the only means of resolving the question, Security Council 
president's statement containing considerate contents would 
implant patience for constructive dialogue among the parties 
involved and would thus make it possible to resume dialogue." 
  He said the summit between Presidents Kim and Jiang did not 
discuss the issues of the Team Spirit and Patriot missiles. 
  "But, China's policy is against any acts of threatening 
stability and building up tension on the Korean peninsula, such 
as the staging of a military exercise and deployment of Patriot 
missiles," Wu said. 
  Stating that President Kim's visit to China was highly 
successful, the spokesman said South Korea and China will 
closely cooperate in the economic and trade areas based on the 
mutual understanding made through a series of meetings between 
President Kim and Chinese leaders. 

</TEXT>

