<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Leaders To Attend UN Summit in Denmark </H4>
<F P=102> OW3103093594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0919 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3103093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 31 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese leaders 
will lead a high-level delegation to attend the United Nations 
world summit for social development to be held in Denmark in 
March 1995, a Foreign Ministry spokesman said here this 
afternoon. 
  Speaking at a weekly press conference spokesman Wu Jianmin 
said the UN world summit will be an "important event" which 
provides the world leaders with a good opportunity to explore 
together ways to promote social development. 
  It will also contribute to further international cooperation 
in this field, Wu added. 
  He noted that China supports the convocation of this summit 
and has taken an active part in its preparation in the UN 
organizations. 
  "We have set up a preparatory committee and are engaged in a 
number of activities, including a nationwide conference on 
social development, drafting the national report on China's 
social development, formulating the outline of China's social 
development, an exhibition on the achievements in social 
development after the founding of the People's Republic of China 
and an international symposium," he said. 
  The Chinese delegation to attend the summit will carry out 
active and constructive cooperation with other countries and 
will work hard for positive results of the summit, the spokesman 
said. 

</TEXT>

