<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Urges South African Parties To End Violence </H4>
<F P=102> OW3103091994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0905 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3103091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 31 (XINHUA) -- A Chinese Foreign 
Ministry spokesman today expressed the hope that all parties 
concerned in South Africa will take practical measures to end 
violence. 
  Asked to comment on the recent aggravation of violence in 
South Africa at a weekly news conference here this afternoon, 
spokesman Wu Jianmin said that the recent aggravation of the 
violent conflicts in some regions of South Africa has aroused 
concern of the international community. 
  "China always firmly supports the peace process of South 
Africa and hopes all parties concerned in South Africa will 
overcome their differences through negotiations, take practical 
measures to end violence, so as to ensure a smooth general 
election and join hands in working for a new South Africa in 
which all races are equal," Wu said. 

</TEXT>

