<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Mongolian Foreign Minister To Visit 6-11 Apr </H4>
<F P=102> OW3103084094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0821 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3103084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 31 (XINHUA) -- Tserenpiliyn 
Gombosuren, minister of external relations of the State of 
Mongolia, will pay an official visit to China from April 6 to 11 
at the invitation of Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister 
Qian Qichen. 
  A Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman made the announcement 
here today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-4517 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi062_a_94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-062 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  31 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Romania Urges DPRK, U.S. To Resume Talks on Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3103040594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0340 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3103040594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Romania today urged 
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), the United 
States and South Korea to resume talks over the nuclear issue. 
  A spokesman for the Romanian Foreign Ministry said that the 
nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula should be a basic topic 
for inter-Korean dialogue and that steps now should be taken to 
ease tension in the region. 
  The spokesman said that any signatory to the nuclear 
Nonproliferation Treaty has responsibilities to comply with its 
international commitment unconditionally. 
  Complying with the agreement between the International 
Atomic 
Energy Agency (IAEA) and the DPRK, including the acceptance of 
nuclear inspections, will help with the creation of peace and 
security in the Korea peninsula, he said. 
  To this end, the talks between the DPRK, the U.S. and South 
Korea must be resumed, the spokesman added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

