<H3> <TI>   Rong Yiren Meets Former U.S. Under Secretary Kimmitt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3103092194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0758 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3103092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 31 (XINHUA) -- Chinese 
Vice-President Rong Yiren said here today that the maintenance 
of good Sino-U.S. ties is in line with the interests of the two 
peoples and is essential to world peace and stability. 
  He said this while meeting with visiting former U.S. Under 
Secretary of State and managing director of Lehman Brothers, 
Robert M. Kimmitt, this morning. 
  Rong expressed his hope that people from the two nations 
would broaden contacts and understanding through various 
channels and improve bilateral cooperation of friendship in all 
fields. 
  The vice-president also briefed the guest on China's reform 
and opening drive, saying that business people, including those 
from the [United] States, are welcome to conduct economic and 
trade cooperation in China. 
  Kimmitt said that he was glad that Lehman Brothers has the 
opportunity to cooperate with China and he hoped this 
cooperation would be promoted. 
  Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Liu Huaqiu attended the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

