<H3> <TI>   Bank of China Reportedly `Doing Well' in Kazakhstan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3103043694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0347 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3103043694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Almaty, March 30 (XINHUA) -- The Bank of China is 
doing well in Almaty, with business of more than 30 million U.S. 
dollars in 1993, its first year of operation in the capital of 
Kazakhstan. 
  The Bank of China, the first foreign bank allowed to operate 
here, handles savings accounts and time deposits, and offers 
other security and financial services. 
  The bank now has over 200 customers, and total deposits of 
more than one million dollars. 
  The Bank of China has remitted 20 million dollars for its 
customers since it began operating here in April 1993. 
  They also offer financial advice, exchange currencies, and 
assist customers in finding business parters. 
  Director-Manager Xiang Chusheng said the bank will gradually 
expand its business and improve efficiency. 

</TEXT>

