<H3> <TI>   Coal Miners Picket Russian Government House </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003140294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1241 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Over 500 coal miners 
set up pickets around the federal government building in Moscow 
this morning calling for the repayment of debts to help the 
industry survive. 
  The miners, representatives of nearly all the coal mines in 
the country, arrived in Moscow on Tuesday [29 March]. 
  Shouting slogans "Repay our wages!" and "Our families on the 
verge of starvation!", the miners demanded that the government 
repay long standing debts to the coal industry and provide 
appropriate subsidies. 
  The angry miners told reporters that they had sent a letter 
to President Boris Yeltsin and Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin calling them to a meeting with their 
representatives. 
  The picket protest action is scheduled to last until Friday. 

</TEXT>

