<H3> <TI>   NPC Chairman Qiao Shi Meets Nuclear Scientists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003130494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1243 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of 
China's National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met 
with C.H. Llewellyn Smith, director of the European Organization 
of Nuclear Research (EONR), and Professor C.C. Ting, Nobel prize 
winner, here today. 
  The NPC chairman told them that he hoped that the research 
work of EONR will continue to make great achievements. 
  Llewellyn Smith briefed Qiao on EONR's research and training 
work. He expressed appreciation of the cooperation between EONR 
and Chinese scientists, hoping that such cooperation will be 
further enhanced. 
  Llewellyn Smith and his party arrived here on March 27 as 
guests of Song Jian, state councillor and minister in charge of 
the State Science and Technology Commission, and Zhou Guangzhao, 
president of the Chinese Academy of Sciences. 
  During their visit, Llewellyn Smith and his party will 
inspect some research institutions, and hold talks with their 
Chinese counterparts on future exchanges and cooperation in 
high-energy physics. 

</TEXT>

