<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Meets European Nuclear Researcher </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003101194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0938 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin met with C.H. Llewellyn Smith, director of the 
European Organization of Nuclear Research (EONR), and Professor 
C.C. Ting, nobel prize winner, here today. 
  During the meeting, the Chinese president expressed his hope 
that exchanges and cooperation between China and EONR in 
high-energy physics will be further enhanced. 
  Llewellyn Smith briefed Jiang on cooperation links between 
EONR and scientists from various countries, especially its 
cooperation with Chinese scientists. 
  Song Jian, state councillor and minister in charge of the 
State Science and Technology Commission, and Xu Zhihong, 
vice-president of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, took part in 
the meeting. 

