<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rong Yiren, Beijing Mayor Meet European Council Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2903122894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1123 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2903122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 29 (XINHUA) -- Chinese 
Vice-President Rong Yiren met here today with a delegation from 
the Assembly of the Council of Europe, led by its president, 
Miguel Angel Martinez. 
  Extending his welcome to the guests, Rong described the 
relationship between the Assembly of the European Council and 
the National People's Congress of China (NPC) as a "good 
cooperative one." 
  Rong noted that China is a developing country whose people 
hope that it can be built under a peaceful international 
environment, which is essential to the development of Europe and 
Asia as well. 
  The vice-president added that Europe has achieved great 
progress in the economy, science and technology and is 
complementary economically to China. 
  China hopes that its friendly relations and cooperation with 
Europe in the fields of economics and trade, science and 
technology and other fields will be strengthened further, Rong 
said. 
  Martinez said that meetings with and frank exchange of views 
with Chinese leaders during the past two days will be conducive 
to the development of the friendly cooperative relations. 
  Martinez expressed his conviction that without cooperation 
between Europe and China, reconstruction of the world order 
cannot be carried out harmoniously. 
  He said that the purpose of his current visit is to enhance 
mutual understanding and make joint efforts toward the 
establishment of a new world order. 
  Ni Zhifu, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, was 
present at the meeting. 
  Earlier today, Mayor of Beijing Li Qiyan also met with 
Martinez and his party. 
  The delegation was scheduled to visit Shanghai and Xiamen 
and 
wind up its China visit Saturday [2 April]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

