<H3> <TI>   Paper Says DPRK Training Special Commando Unit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2802024294 Seoul SEOUL SINMUN in Korean 28 Feb 94 p 16 </F>
<F P=103> SK2802024294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul SEOUL SINMUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [NAEWOE News Agency report] </F>
  [Text] It has been learned that North Korea established a 
special military unit called "commando unit" [tukkong 
yukchondae] and secretly trains it. Recently acquired documents 
on North Korea show that North Korea selected members of the 
commando unit from the "Nampo Military and Political School" and 
gives them ideological education. The commando unit is composed 
of orphans who have no close relatives. North Korea divided the 
39 members of the commando unit (30 men and nine women) in two 
platoons and gives them spy training to send them to South Korea. 

</TEXT>

