<H4>   Extends Stay Until 4 Mar </H4>
<F P=102> OW2802023994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0230 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2802023994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 28 KYODO -- Chinese Vice Premier Zhu 
Rhongi will extend his stay in Japan by one day until Friday [4 
March], Foreign Ministry officials said Monday. 
  Zhu, in Japan since last Wednesday for talks with Japanese 
leaders, was scheduled to leave on Thursday after visiting 
Osaka, Okayama and Fukuoka Prefectures in western Japan. But 
the Chinese side requested to extend the stay until Friday 
without giving any specific reasons, the officials said. 
  Zhu will return home Friday from Fukuoka, they said. 

