<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Sirivut To Visit Israel, Egypt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2802064894 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0413 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2802064894 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 28 Feb (AKP) -- A delegation led by 
Prince Kromkhun Norodom Sirivut, deputy prime minister and 
minister of foreign affairs and international cooperation, will 
soon pay a visit to Israel and Egypt at the invitations of the 
two countries' foreign ministers. 
  This is the first visit by a Cambodian delegation to the two 
countries since the formation of the Royal Government of 
Cambodia in September 1993. 

