<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Auto Negotiations Issue `Difficult' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0103115394 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 1 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 5 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0103115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Both Japan and the United States have been 
discussing the resumption of vice ministerial negotiations on 
the automobile and auto parts sector to be held under the 
Japan-U.S. framework talks. A senior official in the Ministry of 
International Trade and Industry, however, made clear on 28 
February that it has become difficult to hold the vice 
ministerial negotiations. 
  Japan has asked the United States to hold the vice 
ministerial negotiations when U.S. Commerce Undersecretary 
Jeffrey Garten visits Japan on his tour of Asia, but it has 
replied to Japan that "he would have no time to hold the 
negotiations." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-4683 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas040__a94012" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-040-A </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  1 March 1994 </DATE1>

