<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Ochirbat Discusses Visit to India </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2602184194 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1749 GMT 26 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2602184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 26 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- After 
accomplishing his official visit to India the president of 
Mongolia P. Ochirbat has granted an interview in the plane to 
the special correspondents of the MONTSAME news agency and the 
newspaper "ARDYN ERH". The president announces that he 
considers the outcome of his visit to India as very successful. 
  He particularly points out to the signing of the treaty on 
friendly relations and cooperation between Mongolia and India, 
noting that this treaty defines the basic principles of mutual 
relations of the two countries under new conditions. As the 
President P. Ochirbat says, during the visit signed was a number 
of other documents, defining the principles of cooperation of 
the two countries in concrete branches and directions. In the 
president's view, the sides have got an idea about mutual 
interests in the sphere of economic relations. 
  P. Ochirbat says that the Indian business circles have shown 
a great attention to the Mongolian businessmen, accompanying the 
president during his visit. 
  Answering the questions of the correspondents, P. Ochirbat 
especially points out to the statement of the Prime Minister of 
India N. Rao about coincidence of the open-door policy of 
Mongolia with the policy of India. Concerning financial 
assistance to Mongolia on the part of India, P. Ochirbat points 
out to readiness of the Indian businessmen to render financial 
assistance to Mongolia in realization of big projects. Projects 
will be made concrete during the pending visit of the Indian 
businessman sent to Mongolia in May. 

</TEXT>

