<H3> <TI>   MNDP, MSDP To Boycott Great Hural Meetings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2402201894 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1627 GMT 24 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2402201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, February 24. (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
State Great Hural members from the Mongolian National Democratic 
Party (MNDP) and the Mongolian Social Democratic Party (MSDP) 
will not participate in the parliament work any more on behalf 
of their parties. A decision on this has been adopted by the 
coalitional council of the MNDP and the MSDP. 
  According some leaders of these parties in opposition, this 
means only refusal of the party representative in the 
parliament. An issue about recalling the parliamentarians 
members of these parties from the membership in the State Great 
Hural remains open. 
  The coalitional council, as it is said in its statement, has 
come to such a decision "apropos of the continuing crisis caused 
by disproportionate reflection in the parliament-supreme 
legislative organ of the real placing of political forces in the 
society, violation of the basic provisions of the Constitution, 
the basic principles of the parliament, state system". 

</TEXT>

